external_knowledge:
- 'Strong recommendations' refer to properties with a recommendation score greater than 0.7;
- 'High sold prices' refer to properties sold for more than $150,000;
- 'Overall value exceeding a certain threshold' refers to property types and neighborhoods with an average sale price greater than $150,000.

- 'Good location and low price' implies that the properties are both geographically desirable and economically attractive;
- 'User preferences' indicate that these recommendations are based on the specific criteria and preferences set by the users;
- 'Highly recommended' properties have a recommendation score greater than 0.9;
- 'Specific sizes and features' include average first floor area over 1000 square feet, average second floor area over 500 square feet, average living area over 1500 square feet, more than 2 full bathrooms, more than 1 half bathroom, more than 3 bedrooms above grade, more than 1 fireplace, more than 2-car garage capacity, and a garage area over 500 square feet.

- "Most valuable property" refers to the property with the highest sale price;
- "Average price of its neighborhood" is the average sale price of all properties in the same neighborhood;
- "Number of properties in its neighborhood" is the count of properties in the same neighborhood;
- "Frequency of its visits" is the number of access events recorded for the property;
- "Number of recommendations" is the count of recommendations the property has received.

- "Gems" refer to properties that are highly recommended and valuable;
- "Most affluent neighborhoods" are determined by the highest average sale prices of properties within those neighborhoods;
- "Ranked by their value and appeal" means properties are ranked by their sale price and recommendation score, respectively.

- "First significant investment" refers to the earliest purchase where the sale price is above the average sale price of all properties;
- "Keen interest in multiple properties" indicates that the user has accessed more than 10 properties in the `access_logs` table;
- "Most experienced" is determined by the user having the role 'agent' and being the top result when ordered by `user_id` in descending order.

- 'Top recommendation score' refers to the highest score a property has received from user preferences or algorithms;
- 'Sale duration' refers to the time a property was listed before it was sold;
- 'Living area' refers to the above-grade (ground) living area in square feet;
- 'Access frequency' refers to the number of distinct dates the property data was accessed;
- 'Recommendation frequency' refers to the number of distinct dates the property was recommended.

- The score for each property is calculated using a weighted sum where lot size (0.2), overall quality (0.3), year built (0.1), and sale price (0.4) are the factors;
- The properties are ranked within each neighborhood, and the property with the highest score in each neighborhood is selected;
- The `MAX(property_id)` function is used to select the property ID, which is a common practice when there could be ties in the ranking.

- 'Highly recommended' refers to properties with a recommendation score greater than 0.9;
- 'Excellent condition' refers to properties with an overall quality greater than 6 and an overall condition greater than 4;
- 'Built in the last few decades' refers to properties built after 1990;
- 'Recently remodeled' refers to properties that were last remodeled after 2000.

- 'Highly recommended' refers to properties with a recommendation score greater than 0.9;
- 'Initial asking price' is the sale price listed in the `properties` table;
- 'Final sale price' is the price at which the property was sold, recorded in the `sales` table.

- ' Caught the eye of the agents' refers to properties viewed by users with the role 'agent';
- 'Blooming with a price tag exceeding $150,000' indicates properties with a sale price greater than $150,000;
- 'Admired more than twice' means the property has been viewed more than two times by agents.

- "Highly rated" refers to properties with a high `overall_qual` and `overall_cond` score;
- "Recommended to more than one user" means the property has been recommended more than once;
- "Top 3" refers to the properties with the highest combined scores of `overall_qual` and `overall_cond`.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(property_id) 
FROM properties 
WHERE overall_qual > 5 AND sale_price > (SELECT AVG(sale_price) FROM properties);
